member.summary:
Composes the given projection lambdas into a single projection which only references the necessary selected colums. Thus, if you have something like
query.Select(c => new { CompanyName = c.Company.Name, c.Name }) .Where(t => t.CompanyName != null >> t.CompanyName.Length > 0) .Select(t => t.Name);
we might naively generate a projection like c => new { CompanyName = c.Company.Name, c.Name }.Name. This will fail when executed, because we will not have selected any columns from Company.
